video:video.video:description: People braved below-zero weather in Minneapolis Friday for a massive protest against the Trump administration's immigration crackdown.

video:video.video:title: President Trump dismisses concerns about bruised hand, says he “clipped it on the table"
video:video.video:description: U.S. President Donald Trump dismissed concerns about new bruising visible on his left hand, saying he “clipped it on the table” and applied cream to it.

video:video.video:title: Trump says US is moving fleet of ships toward Iran
video:video.video:description: President Donald Trump said he is moving a fleet of ships towards Iran, “just in case” it wants to take action against the country over its crackdown on protesters.

video:video.video:title: Long checkout lines in Georgia grocery store as winter storm looms
video:video.video:description: Lines at checkout were longer than usual in Krogers and Walmarts around metro Atlanta as people stocked up on weekend supplies ahead of what forecasters say could be a nasty winter storm (AP Video: Emilie Megnien)

video:video.video:title: How accurate are weather apps, really?
video:video.video:description: That snowflake icon on your smartphone app might be quick and handy — it just might not be as accurate as a human when the weather gets rough.

video:video.video:title: Stores selling out of ice melt, shovels ahead of winter storm
video:video.video:description: Shoppers in Kentucky and Oklahoma are among those who've been loading up on supplies and shovels because of a massive winter storm that threatens about half the U.S. population heading into the weekend.

video:video.video:title: UK PM Starmer slams Trump for "insulting" comments about non-US NATO troops in Afghanistan
video:video.video:description: U.K. Prime Minister Keir Starmer has urged U.S. President Donald Trump to apologize for his false assertion that troops from NATO countries — other than Americans — stayed away from the front line during the war in Afghanistan.

video:video.video:title: Key representatives of U.S., Russia and Ukraine meet for peace talks in Abu Dhabi
video:video.video:description: Friday's talks are the first known time officials from Trump's administration simultaneously meet with Ukrainian and Russian negotiators.

video:video.video:title: Protesters show up en masse to demand ICE leave Minnesota amidst federal crackdown
video:video.video:description: Thousands gathered, despite Arctic temperatures, in downtown Minneapolis to protest the Trump administration's immigration crackdown.

video:video.video:title: Gaza displaced line up at an Al-Muwasi field kitchen amid food shortages and spiking prices
video:video.video:description: Displaced people in Al Muwasi, in the southern Gaza Strip, lined up on Friday at a soup kitchen to collect a pot of cooked rice, that for some, represents the only hot meal they have during the day.

video:video.video:title: Detroit nonprofit opens doors to homeless population as temperatures drop
video:video.video:description: As bone-chilling temperatures hit Detroit, the Pope Francis Center opened its doors to people experiencing homelessness, offering warm shelter and cots to those seeking refuge from the cold.

video:video.video:title: Thousands in downtown Minneapolis protest ICE despite Arctic cold
video:video.video:description: Despite a severe blast of Arctic air, thousands turned out for a large protest in downtown Minneapolis against the Trump administration's immigration crackdown Friday.

video:video.video:title: Singing contest in Rio prison provides creative outlet for women behind bars
video:video.video:description: A group of Brazilian women behind bars applied makeup, donned gowns and competed in a singing contest held on Friday in a Rio de Janeiro prison, during an event designed to spotlight talents and boost confidence ahead of the detainees’ release.

video:video.video:title: Car crashes into Detroit-area airport entrance, injuring 6
video:video.video:description: A car crashed through the entrance of the Detroit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport on Friday evening, striking a ticket counter and injuring six people, airport officials said.

video:video.video:title: Freezing and in the dark, Kyiv residents are stranded in tower blocks as Russia targets power system
video:video.video:description: Kyiv is facing prolonged winter power outages as Russian missile and drone attacks continue to damage Ukraine’s energy infrastructure.

video:video.video:title: Amy Redford at Sundance: My father built 'a nest, not an empire'
video:video.video:description: Amy Redford paid tribute to her father at the first Sundance film festival since his death, saying Robert Redford built "a nest, not an empire." (Jan. 23)

video:video.video:title: Lost after Adamuz train crash, Boro the dog found safe and sound
video:video.video:description: After back-to-back fatal train crashes sent shockwaves through Spain, some good news arrived Thursday: Boro, the missing dog, was found.

video:video.video:title: Protesters rally in Portland demanding 'ICE out of Maine'
video:video.video:description: Several hundred people gathered in Portland’s Monument Square despite frigid and windy conditions to protest Immigration and Customs Enforcement’s sweeping ongoing action in Maine, .

video:video.video:title: Ed Harris celebrates wife Amy Madigan's Oscar nomination
video:video.video:description: Ed Harris is celebrating independent film at Sundance — and his wife Amy Madigan's Oscar nomination for her role in the horror film "Weapons." (Jan. 23)
